reviews.text: Definitely worth the trip and a fun historical city to spend an evening in. There is a reason this Capitol Building is considered one of the most renowned in the US. Definitely take the free tour, is is not very long and very informative. Plus you get to see some cool governmental areas of the Capitol not always open to the public.
Really cool and free activity. If you live nearby and haven't been, I recommend checking it out. Lots of great history!
So much too see. Beautiful building. It is under refurbishment or cleaning but it is well worth a visit. Got to see the governor
Nice museum located on the first floor of the Capitol building. It has the most beautiful musical instrument that I have ever seen... an inlaid zither. Be sure to see it. Very well done exhibits.
It was amazing they have alot of nice things about the history of Missouri. They have a great section about ww1. It was a lot of fun.

Great historic site. The decor, enviroment and overall feel of this place was spot on. My children and I loved it. Entertaining and educational. The staff were very helpful and knowledgeable. Overall very family friendly and a great experience!
Because of flooding Amtrak was not able to run that day.  So Windstar ran the River Run.  It was my pleasure to drive it.
Good time filler between tours.
Free and always worthwhile exhibits featuring various aspects of Missouri history. Great for all ages and interests!
Cool historic place that shows history of railroad in Jefferson City.
DO NOT POSSESS Q-TIPS IN MISSOURI
You should check out there memuseum.. cool artifacts.. maybe small but still a lot of information about the state patrol an event that had happened
Very helpful place

2 thumbs up to everyone at the state capitol!!! life unlimited from liberty mo traveled to the capitol with our individuals with special needs  yesterday  for disability rights day. I must say that this year everyone welcomed us with open arms. we had a really nice time. keep up the good work!!!! makes me proud be to able to brag on my hometown!!!! jay pride native 05!!!! much better then last year!!!!!!

There is a lot of cool historical sites and monuments to check out here. Unfortunately our trip was spontaneous and during the winter. Everything was closed and the Capitol building was under renovation and completely fenced off. We still got to check out a lot of the monuments and other cool sites. There is an awesome view of the Missouri River and great places for taking pictures.

It was great seeing both the House and the Senate lounges. The Thomas Hart Benton paintings in the house lounge were spectacular. The capital is a Missouri treasure that all Missourians should make an effort to go visit!
This place is beautiful! We loved the free tour and the museum inside. Even with the renovations going on the outside, it was well worth the visit.
Great and beautiful building with lots of interesting history! Recommended!
Excellent opportunity to learn more about Missouri presented here.
Excellent place to enjoy nature and fantastic educational building. I went two times during my stay in town!
This was a great place to visit. The staff there was so friendly and knowledgeable.  The trails were clear, the exhibits and displays were fun and informative.
I love it. I have been there for years

We love to explore here.  Their programs for kids are so fun and informative.  Staff is very friendly and knowledgeable.  They always have a large array of events for all ages.  I just wish they shared events on social media.
A nice, quiet, informative look into the history of Wyoming. Really pretty fascinating to see the layout. I think my favorite room was the Sun Porch on the 2nd floor.
My husband and I loved going to this house and it’s free!! Employees are very kind and friendly. You should definitely go!!
This place was a hidden gem. Free entry & really neat to see.

Came in there almost at 5pm while passing through Cheyenne. Nevertheless the local museum workers were happy to let us in and even gave us a short tour -- all for free. Really nice and somewhat educational place to visit with a family.
Amazing place! There are so many cool details.  I'd have to say my favorite part was the music box by the stairs.

Nice place to take photos of all types-family, engagement, senior, wedding, etc. Flowers are well maintained and walkways are clear. Roses are beautiful in the spring. Sometimes can be crowded depending on the time of day/season.
Beautiful and well maintained. Fantastic location for pictures and outdoor weddings.

The memorial gardens or Gov gardens is a very nice place to get pictures. just about every photographer comes here to get nice shots. When the flowers are in full bloom it's very nice to get great shots.

When prom time comes or engagement photos are needed quick this is a great go to. check it out and bring your camera and have a good time. It does get busy in the summer so make sure you plan for the right time.

Your Trustworthy Critic
It looks great but it's just a park to look & around & take pictures in or at least that all the public uses anyway.
Beautifully landscaped grounds. Clean. Well maintained. Very nice place to visit.
Much hard work went in to making this monument a huge success, job well done Janet M and crew. Hopefully we can get the entire country to stop and enjoy the history....
This is nice little memorial. If you visiting the Capitol, it is worth the short detour.
This was a fun and interesting monument to visit. And FREE!!!
Nice quiet place for a stop & a bit of history.
Cool place to bring the family and you can't deny the gorgeous views

Really good cemetery place. It has wide area and comfortable for hiking or jogging.

The grave also well organized. Good place for "the last rest" for all the Korean Heroes during Korean War.
What a beautiful resting place to honor all whom rest here. A heaven on earth!

Place for prayer

Sooo good - don't let the attached gas station fool you.  Great food, good people and fast service. Turkey, burnt ends, baked beans, mac and cheese....done and done!!!

You wouldn't expect to find great barbecue attached to a gas station, but that's what you'll find here. Expect a long line if you go during lunch hour, because the locals love this place. There is seating, but lots of people get takeout. I certainly would not give the place five stars for its ambience, but five stars for sure for the food! Personally, I love the pulled pork. And the French fries. Lots of people like their homemade chips, which come with several seasoning options, but I'm not a great fan of chips.
Man this BBQ is beyond good it is excellent potato salad was good and oh my goodness if you get a chance try the homemade potato chips outstanding service outstanding food
Amazing bbq and I love their different flavored chips.

Wow....the ribs were amazing!  I’m here for work and found this place bc of google reviews and I’m so glad I did!  I’m very likely to eat there again tomorrow night it was so good. I was a little taken aback when I saw it was connected to a convenient store, but so happy I tried it anyway.  Incredible!
Extremely friendly staff and very cool atmosphere even if you don't know the movie.  Expensive but we enjoyed our experience! We had a couple drinks and an appetizer but the menu did look good.

Very famous cafe attracts many tourists all over the world probably due to the movie. There are large groups from the mainland China. Excellent atmosphere. Food ok, seafood is fresh.. Quite good service.

It's an attraction itself. The interior is similar to the movie. Excellent main dish and reasonable price. Take note your bill includes 10% service charge. Service is good but not above average as the restaurant is very busy at dinner time. Reservation is Recommended.
Very pricey but a great experience.  Lovely food. Great wines. Impeccable service.

What a wonderful place to spend a magical evening with your friends/ family / lover. I can't stress how amazing the whole atmosphere is, how great the service is, and how nicely everyone treated us. 
The food was quite decent, it came quickly and was delicious, however not something super crazy. The wine options are plentiful, so I am pretty sure everyone will find something to their liking. 
The restaurant at night becomes very busy, so keep in mind, that booking in advance is a great idea, especially if you are more in a group.

The food and atmosphere is fantastic. A great mix between casual and fine dining. Their frites and aioli are a great appetizer and their lunch, supper and drink specials are always on point. The wait staff is super friendly and will gladly answer questions about their dishes. The prices are a little high but they are definitely warranted because of the food quality.

The restaurant itself is so beautiful and cozy. I love their appetizers, especially the frites and aioli. They switch up their menu with season dishes. I always love their duck. The staff is always polite and professional. If you are a person who doesn’t like your food touching, I would let them know when ordering because they do stack their food.
Terrific food, moderate prices for lunch menu. Attentive service. Elevated palate.

Really nice atmosphere. Beautiful holiday decorations and friendly staff. Fast service. We ordered the brucheta and it was very tasty. Each meal is served with a choice of soup or salad. They did a great job on the salad. I went with the pasta for my main course, it was really great tasting, but completely drowned in the sauce. Almost soup like. The menu is fairly short but very reasonable priced.

I celebrated my 21st birthday here and I am  impressed with the service and food quality in this place!
I will remember this place for a long time and sure will come back once again 
*Dona was very nice and help to make that evening even better, she also put a birthday candle in my dessert 😱
Yoyums is always a favorite stop with my kids. They always have fun flavors and a variety of toppings. You get to build your own dessert and the price is based on the weight.
There is always something for everyone! I just had their raspberry mojito flavor and it was tart and refreshing! As always will keep coming back!
We love to support local businesses and the frozen yogurt is always great.  It is a fun place to go.
Awesome place.  Very friendly,  very tasty.  A must stop kinda place.
Lovvvve the flavors just wish they had the little gogo berries those would get them non stop business !
